{"title_page": "Flemming Tops\u00f8e", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Flemming Tops\u00f8e''' (born 25 August 1938 in [[Aarhus]], [[Denmark]]) is a Danish mathematician, and is emeritus in the mathematics department of the [[University of Copenhagen]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.math.ku.dk/english/staff/faculty/?pure=en/persons/142431|title=Flemming Tops\u00f8e (faculty profile page)|work=Department of Mathematics|publisher=University of Copenhagen|accessdate=April 24, 2020}}</ref> where he has worked since 1964.{{citation needed}}  He is the author of several mathematical science works, among them works about [[analysis]], [[probability theory]] and [[information theory]]. He is the older brother of the engineer [[Henrik Tops\u00f8e]] (born 1944), son of the engineer [[Haldor Tops\u00f8e (1913\u20132013)]] and great-grandson of the crystallographer and chemist [[Haldor Tops\u00f8e (1842\u20131935)]].<ref>{{cite book | last=Larsen | first=Thomas | title=Haldor Tops\u00f8e - a portrait | publisher=Gyldendal Business S\u00e6lges p\u00e5 internettet | year=2013 | isbn=87-02-15378-5 | oclc=865668496 | page=}}</ref>\n\nTops\u00f8e took [[Magisterkonferens]] in mathematics at [[Aarhus University]] in 1962 and [[doctorate]] in 1971 at University of Copenhagen with the [[thesis]] ''Topology and Measure''. He was leader of the [[Danish Mathematical Society]] 1978\u20131982 and dynamic leader of ''Euromath'' 1983\u20131998, a great project about expansion of [[Internet]]-based services to mathematics societies in [[Europe]] and [[Russia]]. He received a Hlavka memorial medal in 1992 and a B. Bolzano honorary medal in 2006 of the [[Czechoslovak Academy of Sciences]] for his mathematical contributions.\n\n==Books==\n*{{cite book | last=Tops\u00f8e | first=Flemming | title=Spontaneous phenomena : a mathematical analysis | publisher=Elsevier Science | publication-place=Oxford | year=1990 | isbn=978-0-323-16038-4 | oclc=843202655 | translator-last=Stillwell|translator-first=John|translator-link=John Stillwell}}\n*{{cite book | last=Tops\u00f8e | first=Flemming | title=Informationsteori | publisher=Gyldendal | year=1973 | isbn=978-87-00-96231-6 | oclc=466446962 | lang=da}}\n*{{cite book | last=Tops\u00f8e | first=Flemming | title=Topology and measure | publisher=Springer-Verlag | publication-place=Berlin New York | year=1970 | isbn=978-3-540-36284-5 | oclc=295009759}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.math.ku.dk/~topsoe/CVny.html|Flemming Tops\u00f8e's homepage}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Topsoe, Flemming}}\n[[Category:1938 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Aarhus]]\n[[Category:University of Copenhagen faculty]]\n[[Category:Danish mathematicians]]\n[[Category:Danish science writers]]\n\n\n{{europe-mathematician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Flemming Tops\u00f8e''' (born 25 August 1938 in [[Aarhus]], [[Denmark]]) is a Danish mathematician, and is emeritus in the mathematics department of the [[University of Copenhagen]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.math.ku.dk/english/staff/faculty/?pure=en/persons/142431|title=Flemming Tops\u00f8e (faculty profile page)|work=Department of Mathematics|publisher=University of Copenhagen|accessdate=April 24, 2020}}</ref> where he has worked since 1964.{{citation needed}}  He is the author of several mathematical science works, among them works about [[analysis]], [[probability theory]] and [[information theory]]. He is older brother of the engineer [[Henrik Tops\u00f8e]] (born 1944), son of the engineer [[Haldor Tops\u00f8e (1913\u20132013)]] and great-grandson of the crystallographer and chemist [[Haldor Tops\u00f8e (1842\u20131935)]].<ref>{{cite book | last=Larsen | first=Thomas | title=Haldor Tops\u00f8e - a portrait | publisher=Gyldendal Business S\u00e6lges p\u00e5 internettet | year=2013 | isbn=87-02-15378-5 | oclc=865668496 | language